Set Up Azure Machine Learning:

Step 1: Search for Azure Machine Learning in the search bar.
Step 2: Fill in the required details:
a. Name
b. Resource group
c. Storage account
d. Region
e. Key Vault
f. Application Insights
g. Container Registry
h. Subscription
Step 3: Under Networking, choose Public.
Step 4: For Identity, select User assigned identity if already set up, or it will be created automatically for the required services.
Step 5: Click on Review + Create.
Step 6: After deployment, navigate to the resource group to view your Azure ML resource.

Access Azure Machine Learning Studio:
Step 1: Once deployed, go to the resource overview.
Step 2: In the overview, click on Launch ML Studio.
Step 3: Access your Azure Machine Learning Studio to start working on your ML models.
